				<div class="body">
					<p>It's nice to see route recognition show up in Cake, that makes it much more flexible for larger applications. Also, You have some good examples of its usage.</p>
<p>Some would sway against using PHP to build the link, thinking it is easier to just use HTML - but the flexibility you get in the long run makes it worth it. You can change routes without worrying about changing a ton of links (not that I recommend changing your URL structure often, but for development purposes).</p>
<p>I thought I saw mentioned somewhere that Cake was getting RESTful support? (or maybe they already have). Does that get bundled with recognized URL's as well?</p>
