				<div class="body">
					<p>Daniel: Pretty sure the Router will use the first matching route (this goes for normal routing as well as reverse routing). Thats why you should always define your most specific routes first.</p>
<p>Nate: CakePHP has full REST support now, I'll do a post on it soon. Meanwhile check Router::mapResources($controller) to get an idea of how it works.</p>
